{
  "title": "Distortion of regional old-age mortality due to late-life migration in the Netherlands?",
  "abstract": "Regional mortality differences are an important public health indicator and can serve as the basis for population forecasts and local planning. Health-related migration at old age may distort observed regional mortality.",
